<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="Aptus.Explanation.ShoulderPress"
             Title="ShoulderPress">
    <ScrollView>
        <StackLayout Margin="0,0,0,0" BackgroundColor="#A9B3B9" >

            <Label
                Text="SHOULDER PRESS"
                FontSize="25"
                FontFamily="Arial"
                FontAttributes="Bold"
                TextColor="White"
                HorizontalOptions="Center"
                VerticalOptions="Center"
                Margin="0,50,0,20">
            </Label>

            <StackLayout
                BackgroundColor="White"
                WidthRequest="300"
                HeightRequest="1"
                Opacity="0.5">
            </StackLayout>

            <Frame
                CornerRadius="30"
                WidthRequest="300"
                Margin="0,20,0,0"
                BorderColor="Transparent">
                <Image
            Source="shoulderpress.pmg"></Image>
            </Frame>

            <Label
                Text="HOW TO PERFORM"
                FontSize="20"
                FontFamily="Arial"
                FontAttributes="Bold"
                TextColor="White"
                HorizontalOptions="Center"
                VerticalOptions="Center"
                Margin="0,50,0,20">
            </Label>
            <StackLayout
            BackgroundColor="White"
            WidthRequest="300"
            HeightRequest="1"
            Opacity="0.5">
            </StackLayout>

            <Frame
            CornerRadius="30"
            WidthRequest="300"
            Margin="0,20,0,0"
            BorderColor="Transparent"
            Padding="20"
            BackgroundColor="White"
            Opacity="0.8">
                <Label
        Text="First, select your dumbbells. Don’t go overboard on the weight here, because this is an exercise that suddenly feels very tough halfway through a set. You almost want to feel like you’ve picked too light a weight for the first couple of reps. Opting for too heavy a weight can also mean you risk injury to your shoulders if your form gets sloppy as a result of the load.

Hold the dumbbells by your shoulders with your palms facing forwards and your elbows out to the sides and bent at a 90° angle. Without leaning back, extend through your elbows to press the weights above your head. Then slowly return to the starting position."
FontSize="15"
FontFamily="Arial"
TextColor="#252525"
Padding="10,10,10,10"></Label>
            </Frame>
        </StackLayout>

    </ScrollView>
</ContentPage>